content:
Send a static file as a bot message. For example, send a PDF of a form or schedule for an event. Or send an image to help with instructions or troubleshooting.

Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To use this feature:

Customize Application
Modify Metadata
Manage Bots

Upload a file from your computer or from Salesforce as an asset file.
From Files home, go to Libraries | Asset Library.
Click Upload Asset File. Enter a file name and an API name.

Make the file visible to customers outside of your organization by selecting Let guest users see this asset file on public and login pages.
Save your changes.

Navigate to the Bot Builder. Click Dialogs, and then select the dialog that you want to send a file from.
From the Dialog Component Library, drag the File dialog step onto the canvas.
In the Step Properties panel, in the File Interaction field, select Send File.
Enter the name of your file to search for and select it.

Save your changes. Then when you're ready, activate your bot.
title: Building Einstein Bots in Service Cloud
